{"article_id":"bERC76vCCBvogsyG","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Senate Republicans will hold a vote on an Obamacare repeal bill next week ,","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"leaders announced Wednesday ,","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"attempting one final Hail Mary play","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"to kill off the 2010 law","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"before the chamber runs out of time .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"While they don ' t appear to have secured enough votes yet ,","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"the announcement by Majority Leader Mitch McConnell , Kentucky Republican , will put pressure on the handful of holdouts to either get on board","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"or else explain to the party ' s conservative base why they are standing in the way","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"of fulfilling a campaign promise .","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"President Trump said","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"the bill \" has a very good chance \" at passing .","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"\" Certainly we ' re at 47 or 48 ... senators ,","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"and a lot of others are looking at it very positively , \"","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"he said .","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"Questions about the repeal effort followed the president to New York ,","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"where he was meeting with world leaders on the sidelines of the U.N. General Assembly .","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"Mr. McConnell ,","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"who has been burned twice so far this year on failed floor showdowns over repeal bills ,","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"was reluctant to forge ahead","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"without a guarantee","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"that he could muster the votes this time .","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"But the White House has pushed for a vote ,","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"and Mr. Trump took to Twitter","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"to goad holdouts to back the plan ,","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"sponsored by Sen. Lindsey Graham , South Carolina Republican , and Sen. Bill Cassidy , Louisiana Republican .","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"\" I hope","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"Republican Senators will vote for Graham-Cassidy","depth":13},{"id":27,"text":"and fulfill their promise","depth":14},{"id":28,"text":"to Repeal & Replace ObamaCare .","depth":15},{"id":29,"text":"Money direct to States ! \"","depth":15},{"id":30,"text":"Mr. Trump tweeted .","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"The bill would pool money","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"being used","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"to subsidize Obamacare customers","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"and expand Medicaid in parts of the country","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"and siphon it back to the states as block grants .","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"All told ,","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"the plan would slash federal funding to the states by $ 215 billion through 2026 ,","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"a Washington-based consultancy said Wednesday in a study","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"that found","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"less than a third of states would have an increase in funding","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"compared with current law .","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"Avalere Health said","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"34 states and the District of Columbia would face federal cuts","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"- seven of them would lose more than $ 10 billion -","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"while 16 states would receive more money .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"\" The Graham-Cassidy bill would significantly reduce funding to states over the long term , particularly for states","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"that have already expanded Medicaid , \"","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"said Caroline Pearson , senior vice president at Avalere .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"\" States would have broad flexibility","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"to shape their markets","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"but would have less funding","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"to subsidize coverage for low- and middle-income individuals . \"","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"Those numbers could undermine the bill ,","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"with a number of Republican governors complaining","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"that they have become too attached to the federal cash .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"Five Republican governors signed onto a bipartisan letter Tuesday","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"opposing the bill ,","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"and The Associated Press reported Wednesday","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"that New Jersey Gov . Chris Christie , a Republican and Trump ally , also opposes it","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"because it would take money away from his state .","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"West Virginia","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"- solid Trump country -","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"is expected to lose $ 1 billion by 2026","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"thanks to less federal money","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"to support its Medicaid program .","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"Florida and North Carolina , two other Trump states , would lose funding","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"partly because so many of their residents had signed up","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"and received subsidies","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"to buy plans on Obamacare ' s exchanges .","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"Still , Republican-led states in the Southeast and Midwest generally do better than Democrat-led states ,","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"according to the Avalere study .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"California , for example , would lose nearly $ 80 billion in projected money from federal taxpayers over the next decade .","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"House Minority Leader Nancy Pelosi , California Democrat , called the plan a \" stinkeroo \"","depth":5},{"id":74,"text":"and said","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"she would try to rally blue-state Republicans to join Democrats in opposition","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"if a bill emerges from the Senate .","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"\" I don ' t see how they could vote for it , \"","depth":5},{"id":78,"text":"Mrs. Pelosi said .","depth":5},{"id":79,"text":"The bill ' s supporters , however , say","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"it would shift power from Washington to the states ,","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"giving them flexibility","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"to tailor coverage mandates to their own needs .","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"But the bill is a break with other Republican repeal efforts ,","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"which replaced Obamacare ' s exchange subsidies with less-generous tax credits","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"and slowly scaled down federal funding for states","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"that expanded Medicaid .","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"\" The bill ' s repeal of certain provisions of the Affordable Care Act","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"( ACA )","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"are more disruptive for most states than prior Republican efforts , \"","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"said Fitch Ratings , a credit agency .","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"The main insurers lobby , America ' s Health Insurance Plans , said","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"it opposes Graham-Cassidy","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"because it doesn ' t do enough","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"to bolster the private markets and Medicaid","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"or protect sick customers .","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"It also fails to repeal the tax on health insurers","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"or prevent states from pursuing government-run single-payer systems ,","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"the lobby said .","depth":7},{"id":99,"text":"Sen. Rand Paul , Kentucky Republican , said","depth":7},{"id":100,"text":"he opposes the plan","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"because it doesn ' t go far enough","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"in gutting Obamacare .","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"He is the only member of the 52-seat Republican majority","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"to announce his opposition to the bill .","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"Among other Republican holdouts , Sens . Susan M. Collins of Maine , Lisa Murkowski of Alaska and John McCain of Arizona haven ' t said","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"how they will vote .","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"The trio linked arms with Democrats in July","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"to kill a limited repeal bill","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"designed to prolong the debate .","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"Ms. Collins told CNN","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"that she was disappointed to see a bipartisan effort","depth":13},{"id":112,"text":"to bolster insurance markets","depth":13},{"id":113,"text":"stall in the Senate Health , Education , Labor and Pensions Committee .","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"Ms. Murkowski has said","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"she is trying to calculate the potential impacts of Graham-Cassidy on her state .","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"Mr. McCain told Politico on Wednesday","depth":3},{"id":117,"text":"that he still wanted \" regular order \" - Capitol-speak for an orderly and open debate","depth":4},{"id":118,"text":"that bubbles up through committees","depth":5},{"id":119,"text":"and compels bipartisanship .","depth":5},{"id":120,"text":"\" Nothing has changed , \"","depth":4},{"id":121,"text":"he told the outlet .","depth":4},{"id":122,"text":"\" If McConnell wants to put it on the floor ,","depth":4},{"id":123,"text":"that ' s up to McConnell . \"","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":247,"left":239,"right":246,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":239,"left":196,"right":238,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":196,"left":137,"right":195,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":137,"left":132,"right":136,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":132,"left":128,"right":131,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":125,"right":127,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":